I was not able to access your raw 837, but hopefully you have de-identified it.<br />
<br />
Your NM1 segments aren't getting recognized because it is using a ZD entity code qualifier that is probably not in the specification.<br />
You would need to add a section in the spec where you expect that loop to appear:<br />
A sample is below.  It would depend on where it is showing up in your X12, is it part of the claim or is it at a higher level than that?<br />
<pre><code>      &lt;Loop LoopId=&quot;2310ZD&quot; Usage=&quot;Situational&quot; LoopRepeat=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
        &lt;Name&gt;REFERRING PROVIDER NAME&lt;/Name&gt;
        &lt;StartingSegment SegmentId=&quot;NM1&quot; Usage=&quot;Situational&quot; Repeat=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
          &lt;EntityIdentifier Code=&quot;ZD&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/StartingSegment&gt;
        &lt;Segment SegmentId=&quot;REF&quot; Usage=&quot;Situational&quot; Repeat=&quot;3&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/Loop&gt;</code></pre>

It looks like you have EntityIds: ZD,  SJ, 77 that are showing up where they aren't expected.<br />
<br />
The LX1 should be recognized, but there is something preceeding it that is throwing it off so that it no longer thinks it's in the claim loop.  If you could just show your sequence of segments Ids from the CLM to the LX1 I might be able to identify without the full raw data.<br />
<br />
LIN should show up within a service line so it might be the same issue if you show your sequence from LX1 to the LIN that should be enough to troubleshoot the issue.<br />
